# AI Feature Patterns

## API Routes — Streaming

All AI API routes use the Vercel AI SDK with streaming. Import from `@ai-sdk/anthropic`:

```ts
// app/api/chat/route.ts
import { streamText } from "ai"
import { anthropic } from "@ai-sdk/anthropic"
import { buildSystemPrompt } from "@/lib/ai/system-prompt"

export async function POST(req: Request) {
  const { messages } = await req.json()

  const result = streamText({
    model: anthropic("claude-3-5-haiku-20241022"),
    system: buildSystemPrompt(),
    messages,
  })

  return result.toDataStreamResponse()
}
```

## System Prompt Construction

System prompt builders live in `lib/ai/`. Import all content from the barrel `@/content`:

```ts
// lib/ai/system-prompt.ts
import { projects, bio, skills } from "@/content"

export function buildSystemPrompt() {
  return `You are an AI assistant for ${bio.name}'s portfolio...

Projects: ${projects.map(p => `${p.title}: ${p.description}`).join("\n")}
Skills: ${skills.map(s => s.name).join(", ")}
`
}
```

## Client-Side Chat

Chat UI lives in `components/chat/` — all files are `"use client"`. Use `useChat` from `@ai-sdk/react`:

```tsx
"use client"
import { useChat } from "@ai-sdk/react"

export function ChatWidget() {
  const { messages, input, handleInputChange, handleSubmit, status } = useChat({
    api: "/api/chat",
  })
  // status: "ready" | "submitted" | "streaming" | "error"
}
```

## Semantic Search (Embeddings)

Embedding helpers live in `lib/embeddings/`. The search API route at `app/api/search/route.ts` accepts a `{ query: string }` body and returns ranked project results:

```ts
// lib/embeddings/ handles:
// - generateEmbedding(text) → number[]
// - cosineSimilarity(a, b) → number
// - Precomputed embeddings loaded from content/embeddings.json at runtime
```

After adding a new project to `content/projects.ts`, regenerate embeddings:
```bash
npm run seed:embeddings
```

## Caching Expensive AI Calls

For deterministic AI calls (e.g. project summaries), use the `"use cache"` directive:

```ts
async function getProjectSummary(projectId: string) {
  "use cache"
  const result = await generateText({ model: anthropic("claude-3-5-haiku-20241022"), ... })
  return result.text
}
```

## Error Handling

Wrap all AI route handlers — surface errors as structured JSON, not raw throws:

```ts
try {
  const result = streamText({ ... })
  return result.toDataStreamResponse()
} catch {
  return Response.json({ error: "AI unavailable" }, { status: 503 })
}
```
